subSubSection.paragraph:
Pleon and telson triangular in males (
Fig. 2C
) and broadly ovate in females (
Fig. 2E
). Male pleonites III–VI progressively narrower, lateral margins nearly straight; pleonite VI 2.2 × as broad as long. Male telson 1.3 × as broad as long, with blunt apex (
Fig. 2C
).
